This is one dog you would not want in your cricket team. 
Lovable Husky and Malamute cross, K'eyush does not seem to have inherited the fetch gene and even appears to be clapping his hands in anticipation. 
Key's owner, Jodie Barnard from Brixham, Devon, started snapping her clumsy pooch when she decided his entertaining attempts of fetch had to be shared. 
In the video graphic designer and illustrator Jodie desperately tries to teach her pet to play fetch but he drops it EVERY time. Read More Key misses yet another throw of the ball (Photo: Caters) 
The 31-year-old said: "He's always been hit and miss with catch, more miss than hit. 
"I think he has bad timing, closes his mouth too soon or not soon enough and tries to catch with his paws. 
"I also think he sometimes fails on purpose because it makes me laugh." Read More Although he's rubbish at fetch he's still adorable (Photo: Caters) Read More Cruel wildlife traffickers 'selling hundreds of orphaned baby chimps after gunning down their parents' Jodie Barnard, 31, with pet husky, Key (Photo: Caters) 
Jodie, who runs her own company, Designed by Boo has had Key who turns three-years-old this Spring, since he was just eight-weeks-old. 
"He does occasionally catch, and looks as surprised as he is smug when he does. 
"He never fails to make me laugh, I couldn't imagine not having him. He's a born entertainer and a clown at heart!" Like us on Facebook
